Sentencas: Adherent, porous and catalytically active composite films of Nio-SDC (Ce0.8Sm0.2O9), cermet were synthesized by spray pyrolysis technique at substrate temperature 350 degrees C and annealing temperature 500 degrees C. X-ray diffraction studies confirmed the formation of composite film with separate phases corresponding to cubic NiO and SDC.
Titulo: Studies on spray deposited NiO-SDC composite films for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SEM study has shown the formation of non-uniform film consisting of three-phase boundaries between pores, NiO and SDC phases.
Titulo: Studies on spray deposited NiO-SDC composite films for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: EDAX studies revealed the presence of Ce, Sm and Ni elements in the film.
Titulo: Studies on spray deposited NiO-SDC composite films for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: From AFM study, grain size and surface roughness of the film were found to be 30 and 3 nm, respectively.
Titulo: Studies on spray deposited NiO-SDC composite films for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Catalytic activity of the film was studied in the presence of hydrogen and found to increase with increase in temperature.
Titulo: Studies on spray deposited NiO-SDC composite films for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In higher frequency region, the impedance response was a single semicircle, corresponding to the oxygen ion migration in the bulk.
Titulo: Studies on spray deposited NiO-SDC composite films for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Frequency dependent properties, such as AC conductivity, dielectric constant and dielectric loss were also studied.
Titulo: Studies on spray deposited NiO-SDC composite films for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The AC conductivity of the film increased with increase in frequency, showing the conduction through small polaron hopping mechanism, which is favorable for NiO-SDC composite to be used as an anode material in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Studies on spray deposited NiO-SDC composite films for solid oxide fuel cells
